ilog.concert

Interface IloMap

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IloConstraintMap, IloCumulFunctionExprMap, IloIntervalSequenceVarMap, IloIntervalVarMap, IloIntMap, IloIntSetMap, IloIntVarMap, IloNumMap, IloNumSetMap, IloNumVarMap, IloPiecewiseFunctionExprMap, IloStateFunctionExprMap, IloSymbolMap, IloSymbolSetMap, IloTupleMap, IloTupleSetMap

    public interface IloMap
    The superinterface for all maps, allowing to query the size, etc.

    • Method Detail

      • getNbDim

        int getNbDim()
        This method returns the dimension of the map i.e the number of indexers. Example with a map of int: M[1..5][1..2] M.getNbDim( ) returns 2.

      • getSize

        int getSize()
        This method returns an integer specifying the size of the invoking array. An empty array has size 0 (zero). Example with a map of int: M[1..5][1..2] M.getSize( ) returns 5. M.getSub( 1 ).IloMap.getSize( ) returns 2.

      • getTotalSize

        int getTotalSize()
        This method returns the total number of values that are in this array. Example with a map of int: M[1..5][1..2] M.getTotalSize( ) returns 10. M.getSub(1).IloMap.getTotalSize( ) returns 2.
